    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, there's a way to see exactly how much of your payment is going towards interest and how much is going towards the principal. Most loan servicers provide a breakdown of your payment in the monthly statement you receive. You should look for a section that shows the interest portion and the principal portion of your payment. It might be labeled as \"Interest\" and \"Principal\" or something similar. By looking at this breakdown, you can see exactly how much of your payment is being used to pay off the interest and how much is going towards reducing the principal.\n\nIf you're not seeing this information, or if it's not clear, you can always contact your loan servicer and ask for a detailed breakdown. They should be able to provide you with the information you need. Additionally, there are also online calculators and loan amortization calculators that can help you understand how your payments are being allocated over time. These tools can be really helpful in visualizing how the principal and interest portions of your payment change over time.",
